Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAfter many years in political limbo, APGA’s National Secretary of Labaran Maku has returned hopped back into his former party.
Maku, a former Minister of Information in ex-President Goodluck Jonathan’s administration, confirmed this in Lafia, the Nasarawa State capital, on Thursday.
He said his decision to return to the PDP was in response to the yearnings of his people in Nasarawa State.
He dumped the ruling party then to seek his guber ambition in APGA where nothing worked for him since 2015.
